<seg id=1> US Tennis Open going into the third day. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Beijing, September 1st - On August 31st the American Tennis Open began the third day.  Last years champion, Sampras returned for the competition after recovering for more than a month with a foot injury.  He easily defeated his opponent with the score of 3-0 and successfully got into the second round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Sampras, the current first seeded American player has not been seen in any competition since the middle of July.  He is in very good condition after recovering from his foot injury.  He easily defeated the South African Player with the same score 6-2 in three sets within less than half an hour and now will go into the second round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The number 8 seeded Auckland player Naverteroli defeated his opponent with the score of 6-3, 6-4, 6-0 and advanced to the second round. </seg>
<seg id=5> He used this as win as his twentieth birthday present to himself. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> In the woman's competition the second seeded Spanish player Sanchez was challenged by French player Nadia, but Sanchez won eventually by 6-2, 7-6 to advance to the third round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The fifth seeded Japanese player ItaKutz and the ninth seeded American player Mar Phildenas, who was the champion of 1990, Argentina's player Sava Deni all advanced to the third round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Additionally according to the newest reports, the American player Michael Cheung defeated his opponent in the second round by the score of 4-6, 6-2, 6-3, 7-6 and advanced to the third round. </seg>
</p>
